=== TASK ===
# Templates Library

## Overview
Build the Templates Library feature to manage and apply pre-built decision templates (Finishes, Layouts, Change Requests) to speed project creation and decision approval within Archject. This page enables users to browse, search, filter, preview, create/edit templates, import/export, and apply templates to an active project. Templates should support versioning, soft deletes where appropriate, and be integrated with the Project Workspace for quick actions and consistency across decisions, drawings/specs, and client-facing flows.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A centralized Templates Library UI within Archject that allows users to view, search, filter, create, edit, version, import/export, and apply pre-built decision templates. Templates include Finishes, Layouts, Change Requests, Variations, and Permits as opinionated starter templates to accelerate onboarding and standardize decision workflows.

Goals:
- Provide a fast, non-disruptive way to reuse proven decision templates across projects.
- Enable quick application of a selected template to the currently active project with auditable versioned history.
- Offer robust search with multi-faceted filters across projects, decisions, templates, and files.
- Support CRUD operations for Projects, Decisions, Templates, and Files with versioning and soft delete semantics where appropriate.
- Publish a client-facing, branded experience with a clear audit trail, reminders, and exports for decisions.

Connected features:
- Search & Filter Functionality: Global search across projects, decisions, templates, and files with multi-criteria filtering (type, status, date range, owner, tags, client visibility, etc.).
- CRUD Operations for Projects, Decisions, Templates, Files: Create, read, update, delete operations with versioning and soft deletes where appropriate.
- Project Workspace integration: The Templates Library is accessible from a project workspace; applied templates affect the list of Decision Cards, drawings/specs, and project settings; template application triggers versioned decision creation and notifications.

UI elements and behavior:
- Template List: Cards with preview, usage count, status badge, last modified date, and actions (Open, Apply, Edit, Duplicate, Export, Delete/Archive).
- Preview Drawer/Panel: Quick preview of template content, options, and version history.
- Create/Edit Template Modal: Fields for name, description, type (Finishes, Layouts, Change Requests, Variations, Permits), default options, tags, reminder schedule, owner, visibility, and version note.
- Version History Panel: List of versions with diffs, export options, and restore capability (soft or hard restore depending on policy).
- Import/Export Template: Import from file (JSON/XML) or copy from repository; export to standard format for external use.
- Apply Template Button: Applies the selected template to the active project; prompts for scope (which decisions to apply, target phase), and creates versioned decisions with pre-filled options.
- Filters Bar: Multi-select filters for Type, Status, Owner, Tags, Date Range, Project, and Search query. Quick toggles for "My Templates" vs. "All".
- Shared/Client View: If applicable, a client-facing preview link with non-editable template content and a read-only audit trail.

Visual guidance:
- Maintain Archject’s design system: calm, legible, and action-oriented with consistent typography, spacing, and components. Use the 12-column grid, ample whitespace, and clear visual hierarchy. Emphasize search results and template cards with concise previews and actionable affordances.

## Components to Build
- TemplatesLibraryPage
  - Displays header, search bar, filters, template grid/list, and right rail with quick actions.
- TemplateCard
  - Card component showing: title, type pill, preview thumbnail, usage count, last modified, owner, status, and action menu (Apply, Edit, Duplicate, Export, Delete/Archive).
- TemplatePreviewDrawer
  - Side panel or modal showing template content, sample decisions, fields, options, and version history link.
- TemplateEditorModal
  - Create/Edit form with fields: name, description, type, default options, tags, reminder schedule, visibility, owner, version notes.
- VersionHistoryPanel
  - Collapsible panel listing version entries, diff indicators, restore/compare actions, export options.
- ImportExportModule
  - Handles file import (parsing, validation) and export (JSON/XML), including error reporting.
- ApplyTemplateModal
  - Stepper/modal guiding user to confirm scope: target project, decisions to apply, mapping of template fields to project fields, and post-apply actions (notifications).
- FiltersBar
  - Multi-select controls for Type, Status, Tags, Date Range, Owner, Project, and a global search input with keyword highlighting.
- Sidebar/Topbar Integration
  - Ensure seamless navigation with the Project Workspace: access templates, project settings, client share controls, and decision cards list.
- NotificationSystemHook
  - Emit user-facing notifications when a template is applied, versioned, or when imports/exports succeed or fail.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- UI Components:
  - Reusable Card, Button, Input, Select, Tag, Pill, Drawer, Modal, CheckboxGroup, DateRangePicker, and Icon components aligned to the design system.
- Pages & Routes:
  - /projects/{projectId}/templates
  - /templates/{templateId} (Preview/Detail)
  - Modals: Create/Edit, Import/Export, Apply Template
- Interactions:
  - Debounced search, multi-select filters, bulk actions (e.g., export multiple templates), keyboard accessible controls, responsive behavior for mobile and tablet.
- State Management:
  - Use a centralized store (e.g., Redux/Context) to manage templates, versions, filters, current project context, and user permissions.
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA labels, keyboard navigable controls, proper focus management on modals/drawers.
- Data Handling:
  - Local caching of template previews; progressive loading for large template libraries; optimistic UI updates for apply/edit actions with rollback on error.

### Backend
- APIs (no external APIs connected per context, but provide endpoints for internal services):
  - Templates
    - GET /templates?filters... (list with pagination and search)
    - GET /templates/{id} (detail with version history)
    - POST /templates (create)
    - PUT /templates/{id} (update)
    - PATCH /templates/{id} (partial update, e.g., soft delete/restore)
    - DELETE /templates/{id} (soft delete or hard delete based on policy)
    - POST /templates/{id}/duplicate (clone)
    - POST /templates/{id}/export (trigger export, return file)
  - Versions
    - GET /templates/{id}/versions
    - POST /templates/{id}/versions (create new version)
    - POST /templates/{id}/versions/{versionId}/restore
  - Import/Export
    - POST /templates/import
    - POST /templates/export
  - Apply
    - POST /projects/{projectId}/apply-template (payload includes templateId, targetDecisions or mapping rules)
  - Projects/Decisions/Files (intermediate references)
    - CRUD endpoints as existing in the system; ensure relations to templates (ownership, versioning)
- Data Models (schemas):
  - Template
    - id, name, description, type (Finishes, Layouts, Change Requests, Variations, Permits), content (structured object for default options), tags, ownerId, createdAt, updatedAt, version, isArchived, isDeleted, reminderSchedule
  - Version
    - versionId, templateId, number, createdAt, changesSummary, contentSnapshot
  - ProjectTemplateApplyLog
    - id, projectId, templateId, appliedAt, appliedBy, scopeDetail, result
  - FileAttachment
    - id, templateId, filename, fileType, size, uploadedAt
  - Decision
    - minimal fields to support applying templates: id, projectId, templateAppliedId, status, options
- Validation:
  - Template name unique per user or per project scope (depending on policy)
  - Type must be one of allowed values
  - Content must validate against a defined schema for each template type (Finishes, Layouts, Change Requests)
  - Reminder schedule must be a valid cron or human-readable schedule depending on system
  - Versioning must always capture a changesSummary; cannot create a new version without diff against previous
- Security & Roles:
  - Authentication required for all template operations
  - Authorization checks: only project owners, admins, or template owners can edit/delete; apply templates permitted for project members with specific roles
  - Data ownership: templates owned by users or teams; access controlled by project context and global templates policy

### Integration
- Project Workspace coupling:
  - Ensure Template Library fetches template lists scoped to the active project or global templates as configured.
  - Apply Template action triggers creation of Decisions within the active project with pre-filled fields; update Decision Cards in the Project Workspace accordingly.
  - On template apply, emit events for client-visible activity feed, notifications, and audit trail.
- Search & Filter integration:
  - Global search service should query templates, decisions, projects, and files; results should surface templates with highlighted keywords.
  - Filters should support multi-select and compound queries; implement efficient backend query generation.
- Data consistency:
  - Soft delete propagation: archived templates appear in “Archived” filter and are excluded from active application unless restored.
  - Version history display synced with Frontend VersionHistoryPanel.

## User Experience Flow
1. User navigates to a project and opens Templates Library (Project Workspace → Templates).
2. The page loads with a grid/list of available templates. User can:
   - Use the global search to find templates by name, type, tags, or content hints.
   - Apply multi-faceted filters (Type: Finishes/Layouts/Change Requests; Status: Active/Archived; Owner; Date Range; Tags; Project).
   - Click a TemplateCard to open a TemplatePreviewDrawer for quick viewing.
3. User clicks Edit to modify template details in TemplateEditorModal; saves to create a new version.
4. User clicks Import/Export to bring in templates from external sources or export selected templates to a file.
5. User clicks Apply Template on a chosen template:
   - A modal appears to confirm scope: select target decisions to apply, and map fields if necessary.
   - Upon confirmation, the system creates versioned Decisions in the active project filled with template defaults.
   - Success toast/notification is shown; audit log is updated; the Project Workspace updates the Decision Cards accordingly.
6. User optionally creates a new template from a current project decision or from scratch via Create Template flow.
7. All actions (create, edit, apply, delete/archive, duplicate, export) surface in an activity feed and can be exported as part of a Decision Logs export.

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: Schema Summaries
- Template
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - description: string
  - type: enum (FINISHES, LAYOUTS, CHANGE_REQUESTS, VARIATIONS, PERMITS)
  - content: JSON (structured per template type)
  - tags: array<string>
  - ownerId: string
  - projectId: string | null (global vs project-scoped)
  - version: integer
  - createdAt: datetime
  - updatedAt: datetime
  - isArchived: boolean
  - isDeleted: boolean
  - reminderSchedule: string | null
  - attachments: array<FileAttachment>
- Version
  - id: string
  - templateId: string
  - versionNumber: integer
  - createdAt: datetime
  - changesSummary: string
  - contentSnapshot: JSON
- ProjectTemplateApplyLog
  - id: string
  - projectId: string
  - templateId: string
  - appliedAt: datetime
  - appliedBy: string (userId)
  - scopeDetail: JSON (which decisions, mappings)
  - result: string (success/failure)
- FileAttachment
  - id: string
  - templateId: string
  - filename: string
  - fileType: string
  - size: number
  - uploadedAt: datetime

API Endpoints (illustrative)
- Templates
  - GET /templates?projectId=&type=&q=&tags=&archived=0&page=&limit=
  - GET /templates/{id}
  - POST /templates
  - PUT /templates/{id}
  - PATCH /templates/{id}
  - DELETE /templates/{id} (soft delete)
  - POST /templates/{id}/duplicate
  - POST /templates/{id}/export
- Versions
  - GET /templates/{id}/versions
  - POST /templates/{id}/versions
  - POST /templates/{id}/versions/{versionId}/restore
- Import/Export
  - POST /templates/import
  - POST /templates/export (collection)
- Apply
  - POST /projects/{projectId}/apply-template
- Projects/Decisions/Files (existing)
  - Ensure end-to-end linkage when applying templates to create Decisions with pre-filled data.

Security
- Authentication: JWT/OAuth2 as per system standard; all endpoints require auth.
- Authorization: Role-based access control:
  - Admins and Project Owners can manage templates (create/edit/delete/archive, import/export).
  - Project Members can apply templates to their active project and view non-editable content.
  - Clients may view client-facing previews with restricted permissions where applicable.
- Data ownership and visibility policies based on project scope and template scope (global vs project-scoped templates).

Validation
